LAGOS – The Minister of Youths and Sports Development, Sunday Dare, said that the National Stadium pitch in Surulere, Lagos, will be ready for use as from May 2021. Dare noted that the con­tractors handling renova­tion of the pitch and tracks had assured the ministry of early completion of the ren­ovation works as scheduled. He said: “This arrange­ment is under the adoption initiative which is a pub­lic-private model that we developed. We were able to pitch that as a ministry and government to the private sector and we found a philan­thropist and lover of sport, Sir Adebutu Keshington, who was convinced about the proposal. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! He’s somebody that has the youth of this country at heart and he has done so much to support youth sport development. “By extension, we also want to thank Alhaji Aliko Dongote of Dangote Group by providing similar fund for the Moshood Abiola Nation­al Stadium, which should be ready hopefully by March and have our national team play there,” said Dare. Zenith Bank Reinstates Commitment To Sports Dev In 2021 Nigeria Wins Bronze At African Judo Championships In Madagascar Dare assured that a main­tenance template would be on ground to ensure that the facility does not go back to its deplorable state. “The ministry has de­partment of facility and it is building a template for main­tenance of the stadium. We have facility manager from the private sector that will work with our department of facili­ty. Maintaining this is critical and we are going to take it very serious,” he added. National Stadium Surul­ere, Lagos, was used mostly for football matches until 2004. Before, 2004, it served as the home ground for Ni­gerian national teams and hosted several international competitions including the 1980 African Cup of Nations (AFCON) final, the 2000 AF­CON final, and FIFA World Cup qualifying matches. It also served as the main stadi­um for the All-Africa Games (AAG) in 1973. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION